---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  active="about"
  title="About Monica Messer — Author"
  description="From building companies to telling the truth about women's lives. Monica Messer on her second chapter and the inquiry behind The Family Narrative."
>
  <!-- INTRO (Card 9 expanded) -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="split-media">
        <img src="/assets/author-portrait.jpg" alt="Portrait of Monica Messer" class="cover-img portrait" style="max-width:340px;" />
      </div>
      <div class="split-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">About Monica</p>
        <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4.4vw,3.2rem);">From building companies to telling the truth about women's lives.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          For decades, Monica Messer built, led, managed, and measured success. Now her writing
          turns toward what does not show up on a balance sheet: the quiet decisions, hidden costs,
          and private reckonings that shape a woman's life.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>The Family Narrative</em> grows out of that same inquiry — what we choose not to see,
          what it costs to keep performing, and what becomes possible when we finally look.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FIRST CHAPTER — NASDAQ proof -->
  <section class="bg-sand">
    <div class="container split reverse">
      <div class="split-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">The First Chapter</p>
        <h2>A career measured in results.</h2>
        <p>
          Before the novel, there was the work the world could see: companies built, teams led,
          and milestones reached — including the kind of moment that ends with your name on a screen
          in Times Square. That chapter gave Monica a clear-eyed understanding of money, power, and
          the stories institutions tell to protect themselves.
        </p>
        <p>
          It also gave her the questions she writes about now — the ones that live underneath the
          measurable success.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="split-media">
        <img src="/assets/nasdaq.jpg" alt="Monica Messer at the NASDAQ in Times Square" class="cover-img" style="max-width:420px;" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECOND CHAPTER -->
  <section>
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Second Chapter</p>
      <h2>Now, the truth about women's lives.</h2>
      <p>
        Monica writes domestic literary fiction about women at the moment they stop managing
        everyone else's story and begin telling the truth about their own. Her work returns,
        again and again, to clarity, financial awareness, courage, friendship, and the difference
        between loyalty and complicity.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>The Family Narrative</em>, her debut novel, follows Frances Stanton as a divorce filing,
        a university scandal, and a collapsing financial reality force her to question the admired
        family story she has spent decades preserving.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <a href="/the-family-narrative/" class="btn btn-primary">Read About the Novel</a>
        <a href="/newsletter/" class="btn btn-outline">Read My Story</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Newsletter />
</BaseLayout>
